vulnerability.name: USN-5536-1
vulnerability.description: Multiple security issues were discovered in Firefox. If a user were tricked into opening a specially crafted website, an attacker could potentially exploit these to cause a denial of service, spoof the mouse pointer position, bypass Subresource Integrity protections, obtain sensitive information, or execute arbitrary code.

statements.status_notes: Firefox could be made to crash or run programs as your login if it opened a malicious website.
